seed_chunks:
Lantern-keepers called the **Wickward Guild** patrol the listening glow, mending streetlights and selling “safe routes,” yet they secretly bottle the Hollow’s laughter to power ever-hungrier lamps. The **Cartouche Court**—bark-scribes and polite litigants—offers free wayfinding and arbitration of trail-rights, while covertly rewriting the trees’ pale glyphs to erase rival memories and crown a single “true” path. Meanwhile the **Chimebone Choir** wanders as mournful musicians who soothe fear with iron-and-bone melodies, but their hidden work is tuning heartbeats into a key that opens the Hollow’s throat. The Guild hires the Court to legitimize maps; the Court prosecutes the Choir as “noise-criminals”; the Choir sabotages lanterns, making every “safe route” end in a joke.

